node.text: #ad Did you know that @CaciqueInc makes authentic, delicious queso dips? Did you know that combining one of those dips with @CaciqueInc beef chorizo and a few other elements of deliciousness can result in an amazing cheesy, meaty dip that you can enjoy with chips, veggies or even a bread bowl like this? #SeasonTheDay #goautentico

node.title: Jalapeño Chorizo Queso Dip made in a bread bowl!

node.text: Ever wonder what a savory waffle would taste like? I partnered with one of the country’s top authentic Mexican food brands @CaciqueInc to make Elote Waffles a reality using some ingredients that were already in my kitchen. These waffles are made with Crema Mexicana and Ranchero Queso Fresco. Next level flavor. #ad #GoAutentico #SeasonTheDay

node.title: Elote Waffles with corn based waffles and roasted corn

node.text:
Air Fryer Goat Cheese Balls with Spicy Honey. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Divide some goat cheese into 2 inch balls (about 1 oz) and place them in the freezer for 20 minutes
- In one bowl combine 1 cup of all purpose flour with 1 tablespoon of garlic powder, onion powder, and salt
- In another bowl, combine 2 eggs with 1/4 cup of hot sauce 
- An the third bowl, add about 2 cups of panko bread crumbs 
- Coat the cheese in the flour, then the egg wash, then the panko bread crumbs
- Place them back in the egg wash and back in the panko for a double dredge
- Place the cheese balls in the freezer for another 10 minutes
- Put the goat cheese in the basket of an air fryer and spray them with cooking oil 
- Air fry the goat cheese balls at 370 degrees F for 5 minutes
- For the spicy honey, combine 1/4 cup of honey, 1 tablespoon of hot sauce and 1 teaspoon of cayenne pepper
- Drizzle over honey, and garnish with chopped chives

node.text:
Braided Cinnamon Roll Bread aka Cinnamon Roll Challah. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Unroll 2 cinnamon rolls and stack them on top of each other
- Roll them up so they fuse together. Repeat this 2 more times so you have 3 pieces of dough in the shape of a rope
- Line the dough up next to each other, and pinch the tops together
- Fold the right piece of dough over to the left, and the middle piece of dough over to the right. Repeat this until a braided dough is formed
- Cover the dough in egg wash and bake at 375 degrees F for 25 minutes
- Take it out of the oven and cover in the icing it comes with

node.text:
Eggs Benedict In 5 Minutes. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Bring a pot of water to a boil. Add 2 tablespoons of vinegar and 1 teaspoon of salt
- Add the eggs and cook for exactly 5 minutes
- When the eggs are done, transfer them to a bowl of cold water
- When the eggs are cool to touch, crack one side and fit a spoon in between the shell and the egg
- Rotate the egg keeping the spoon in one place until it released the shell
- While the eggs cook, combine 3 egg yolks with 1 tablespoon of lemon juice
- Slowly whisk in 1 tablespoon of melted butter per egg yolk
- Add the bowl of egg and butter to the microwave in increments of 10 seconds until it becomes thick enough to coat the back of a spoon
- Season with salt, pepper and smoked paprika
- Toast a few slices of English muffins and add some smoked ham on top
- Place the 5 minute egg on top of the ham, add some of the hollandaise sauce and garnish with chopped chives
- #neverskipeggday

node.text:
Jalapeño Popper Sticky Buns. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Combine 1 cup of room temperature cream cheese, 1 cup of sharp cheddar cheese, 1 cup of chopped jalapeño, 1 cup of cooked bacon bits, 1 tablespoon of garlic powder, and 1 tablespoon of smoked paprika in a bowl
- Roll out 16oz of your favorite pizza dough and spread the jalapeño popper mixture on top
- Roll it up like a jelly roll and cut it into 9 equal pieces
- Add the cut buns to a greased baking tray 
- Coat the buns in a beaten egg wash 
- Cook at 425 degrees F for 20 minutes
- Eat on their own or cover in cheese sauce

node.text:
Breakfast Pull Apart Bread (Croque Madame) Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Cut wedges along the side of a circular loaf going from the center to the edge making sure not to cut it all the way through
- Stuff each wedge with a slice of smoked ham and 1 tablespoon of grated gruyere cheese
- For the sauce, melt 2 tablespoons of butter and whisk in 2 tablespoons of flour
- When the flour and butter combine, whisk in 1 cup of milk, 1 teaspoon of nutmeg and a bay leaf
- When the mixture bubbles, turn off the heat and whisk in 1 cup of grated parmesan cheese
- Cover the stuffed loaf in the sauce and bake at 425 degrees F for 12-15 minutes
- Take it out, garnish with chopped chives and a fried egg

Gluten Free Banana Fries. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Using a potato masher or ricer, combine 4 mashed bananas in a bowl with 1 teaspoon of nutmeg, 1 tablespoon of cinnamon and 1/2 cup of corn starch
- When the mixture resembles a thick batter, transfer it to a freezer bag and snip the tip
- Squeeze a few strips of the batter into 375 degree F cooking oil and cook for 3 minutes or until they become golden brown and crispy
- Drizzle some of your favorite chocolate ganache and enjoy!
